<p>Mesa residents have access to multiple layers of solar incentives that significantly reduce the upfront cost of solar installation. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) allows homeowners to deduct 30% of their solar system cost from their federal taxes through 2032, when it drops to 26% and then 22% in 2034. Arizona offers additional state-level incentives, including a 25% state tax credit up to \$1,000 for solar installations. Salt River Project provides net metering programs that allow solar customers to receive credit for excess energy produced by their systems, though SRP has implemented demand charges and time-of-use rates that make battery storage increasingly attractive for maximizing savings.</p>

